07/23/2025,748.1209(b)(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,08/21/2025,09/02/2025,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium Low,Yes,Operation staff admitted to taking youth in care to their personal home. ,"The following compliance plan was sent on 08/28/25 by the Administrator.

1. Overnight Stays:
   - Staff will not be allowed to have any children stay overnight outside of the operation.
   - Only under extreme circumstances where safety is involved (e.g., inclement weather, natural disaster, or emergency evacuation) may an overnight stay be considered.
   - In such emergency situations, the LCCA (Licensed Child Care Administrator) must be notified immediately. The LCCA will contact the Conservator to inform them of the situation and ultimately obtain approval before any overnight stay occurs.
2. Day Outings:
   - Day outings will only be permitted when proper staff-to-child ratios are maintained in accordance with Minimum Standards.
   - All activities must be planned in advance and reviewed/approved by the management team.
3. Training & Communication:
   - All staff will be trained on this policy to ensure understanding that overnight stays are prohibited unless authorized through emergency procedures.
   - Staff will also be trained on requirements for day outings, including ratio compliance and management approval.
4. Monitoring & Compliance:
   - The Administrator/LCCA will review outing and visitation logs weekly to ensure compliance with this corrective action plan.
   - Emergency situations and any outings will be discussed during monthly staff meetings to reinforce policy adherence and accountability.
Completion Date
This corrective action plan will be implemented immediately and fully in effect by 8/30/2025
Responsible Party
- LCCA: Oversight and conservator communication
- Administrator/Designee: Policy training and documentation
- All Staff: Compliance with policy and immediate reporting
"
